WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:01.291
(TRAIN HORN BLARES)

00:01.917 --> 00:03.709
ANNOUNCER: This is the final
call for the 0800

00:03.792 --> 00:05.125
to Los Angeles.

00:06.458 --> 00:07.875
FIONA: Are you following me?

00:08.083 --> 00:09.208
-Alice!
-Alice!

00:09.291 --> 00:11.458
You're the very famous
Billy Johnson.

00:11.834 --> 00:12.709
Yeah.

00:13.000 --> 00:15.000
FIONA: I'm really glad
that she doesn't know

00:15.083 --> 00:16.625
about the real reason
you texted her.

00:16.709 --> 00:17.875
BILLY JOHNSON: (THROUGH VIDEO)
My love and I

00:18.125 --> 00:21.000
made a pact that one day,
one of us would text "run."

00:21.083 --> 00:22.500
I can't wait to read the book.

00:22.709 --> 00:24.125
I gave you a lot of money.

00:24.375 --> 00:26.083
I'd quite like some more.

00:26.792 --> 00:29.208
Give me that bag of cash,
because...

00:29.291 --> 00:30.667
(RUBY MOANING THROUGH PHONE)
Billy!

00:30.750 --> 00:32.792
FIONA: I was in your hotel
last night,

00:33.000 --> 00:34.792
and now that I've got
Lawrence's number...

00:35.750 --> 00:38.458
Fiona, Alice,
she isn't following you, okay?

00:38.542 --> 00:40.583
-She's following me.
-(WHISPERS) I gave Alice
the money.

00:40.667 --> 00:43.041
-Oh, you-- No!
-Billy! We're on a train!

00:43.125 --> 00:44.667
She literally
can't have gone far.

00:44.750 --> 00:47.083
-Fiona!
-Fuck you! (YELLS)

00:47.166 --> 00:48.542
(BOTH SCREAM)

00:55.166 --> 00:57.583
Billy:
My love and I made
a pact that one day,

00:57.667 --> 00:59.417
one of us would text "run,"

00:59.500 --> 01:03.291
and if the other person texted
"run" back within 24 hours,

01:04.000 --> 01:07.750
we would meet at Grand
Central Station in New York,

01:07.834 --> 01:09.709
get on a train,

01:09.792 --> 01:11.291
and voom.

01:11.375 --> 01:13.834
One week across America.

01:14.333 --> 01:16.959
At the end of the line,
we'd have to decide

01:17.041 --> 01:18.583
to stay together

01:18.667 --> 01:20.834
or never see
each other again.

01:21.834 --> 01:24.083
November 28th, 2005,

01:24.166 --> 01:27.166
I texted her.
I heard nothing back.

01:27.583 --> 01:31.333
January 12th, 2008,
she texted me,

01:31.417 --> 01:33.625
but I was busy, so

01:33.709 --> 01:36.041
we've never actually done it.

01:37.875 --> 01:41.208
I woke up this morning with
a funny sort of a feeling.

01:42.166 --> 01:45.041
I wondered,
what if today is the day?

01:45.583 --> 01:48.875
What if she would
text back today? So...

01:50.208 --> 01:52.583
I am about to text her,

01:52.667 --> 01:54.959
and if, miraculously,
she texts back,

01:55.041 --> 01:57.625
I'm gonna grab that bag
and leave here,

01:57.709 --> 02:00.417
and I'm gonna meet her
on that platform.

02:02.041 --> 02:04.625
And whatever happens next

02:04.709 --> 02:06.667
will be the premise
of the new book deal

02:06.750 --> 02:09.041
you're about to offer me.

02:09.250 --> 02:11.417
So, you ready?

02:12.458 --> 02:15.417
R... U... N...

02:18.250 --> 02:19.375
(phone beeps)

02:19.458 --> 02:20.667
Yes!

02:20.750 --> 02:21.875
Mm-hmm.

02:21.959 --> 02:24.083
♪ ♪

02:28.917 --> 02:30.500
(train horn blows)

02:30.750 --> 02:32.166
-We can't.
-We have to.

02:32.250 --> 02:34.041
-No, we can't! It's dangerous!
-Yes, we can! Look at me!

02:34.125 --> 02:36.959
-Oh, no, fuck! All right.
No, I don't want to!
-Come on! Go! Go!

02:37.041 --> 02:38.917
-Billy: Ruby!
-(both screaming)

02:39.000 --> 02:40.125
(Billy groaning)

02:40.208 --> 02:41.750
(grunting)

02:43.834 --> 02:46.667
Oh! Yeah!

02:46.750 --> 02:49.583
-(groaning)
-(Ruby laughing)

02:50.417 --> 02:53.917
Baby! That was awesome!

02:54.000 --> 02:55.375
Fuck off.
Fuck, I'm broken.

02:55.458 --> 02:57.625
-No! Stand up.
-Oh, fuck! No, no, no.

02:57.709 --> 02:59.458
(breathing heavily)

02:59.542 --> 03:01.417
-Shake it down.
-Right, yeah. Okay.

03:01.500 --> 03:04.083
-Okay. Okay.
-Oh. Oh no!

03:04.166 --> 03:05.417
My coat's
on that train.

03:05.500 --> 03:07.333
I love that coat.

03:07.917 --> 03:09.083
Oh, come on.

03:09.166 --> 03:10.417
(Billy groaning)

03:10.500 --> 03:13.041
-There she is!
-Oh no, wait, Ruby! Ruby!

03:13.125 --> 03:15.291
(groaning) Ruby. Ruby.

03:16.083 --> 03:17.959
-Ruby--
-Come on.

03:19.417 --> 03:21.250
See? She's an idiot.

03:21.333 --> 03:23.542
-Let's get her.
-Yeah!

03:23.625 --> 03:26.291
-Okay. Easy does it.
-(Billy groans)

03:27.000 --> 03:29.667
(grunt)
I loved that fuckin' coat.

03:29.750 --> 03:32.166
(panting)

03:32.250 --> 03:34.875
(rapid acoustic guitar playing)

03:34.959 --> 03:36.417
(grunts)

03:36.500 --> 03:38.625
♪ ♪

03:39.834 --> 03:43.125
-(grunting)
-Ruby: We're comin' to get you!

03:43.208 --> 03:45.583
Fiona:
I'm gonna call your husband!

03:45.667 --> 03:47.542
Ruby:
That's our money!

03:47.625 --> 03:49.417
You won't get away with it!

03:49.500 --> 03:52.166
Wait, wait, wait. Ruby.
She's-- she's saying
she'll call your husband.

03:52.250 --> 03:53.542
Ruby and Billy:
No!

03:53.625 --> 03:54.750
Fuck you!

03:54.834 --> 03:57.000
-Billy: No!
-Ruby: No!

03:58.375 --> 04:00.792
Fiona:
Oh, why don't you
just fuck off?

04:02.000 --> 04:04.291
Billy:
Fiona, you total bitch!

04:04.375 --> 04:06.458
♪ ♪

04:07.458 --> 04:10.834
-Ruby: Walk faster
or she'll be gone.
-Billy: She won't be gone.

04:13.709 --> 04:16.083
-Fuck. She's gone.
-Shit.

04:16.166 --> 04:17.750
(panting)

04:21.917 --> 04:24.625
Ruby:
How long have you
been working together?

04:24.709 --> 04:26.709
Billy:
Nearly seven years.

04:26.792 --> 04:28.041
She was only
a temp at first,

04:28.125 --> 04:30.709
but then she just
kept on doin' stuff.

04:31.125 --> 04:32.875
She was answering
the phones,

04:32.959 --> 04:34.917
making me tea when
I didn't ask her.

04:35.000 --> 04:36.542
Then she was
doing the schedules,
and pretty soon,

04:36.625 --> 04:38.291
I couldn't scratch my arse
without her help.

04:38.375 --> 04:40.000
She sounds exceptional.

04:40.083 --> 04:42.333
She was. It was
a fuckin' nightmare.

04:43.291 --> 04:46.208
-(sighs)
-Hey, um...

04:48.417 --> 04:50.583
Have you slept with her?

04:52.041 --> 04:54.208
What sort of
a question is that?

04:54.291 --> 04:56.458
-Of course I have.
-Oh.

04:57.083 --> 04:59.291
We were working together
for seven years.

04:59.500 --> 05:00.667
Oh...

05:00.750 --> 05:02.834
It would've been
rude not to.

05:02.917 --> 05:04.458
Mmm.

05:05.959 --> 05:07.542
Billy:
Where is she?

05:08.625 --> 05:09.959
Hey!

05:10.583 --> 05:11.709
Oh fuck.

05:12.750 --> 05:13.959
You think she went in there?

05:15.625 --> 05:17.041
I hope not.

05:17.834 --> 05:19.041
-Let's go.
-Yeah.

05:19.125 --> 05:21.291
(wooden steps creaking)

05:27.166 --> 05:29.375
(insects, birds chirping)

05:32.417 --> 05:34.000
(flies buzzing)

05:34.083 --> 05:36.291
-(knocking)
-Ruby: Hello?

05:38.750 --> 05:40.834
Oh, this is so fucked up.

05:42.792 --> 05:44.291
Hello?

05:47.417 --> 05:48.959
(quietly):
I don't wanna...

06:00.583 --> 06:02.166
Hello?

06:16.375 --> 06:17.625
(creaking)

06:17.709 --> 06:19.625
(gasps)
Someone's upstairs!
Did you hear that?

06:19.709 --> 06:22.000
-(whispers): No. No!
-(whispers): Someone's upstairs!

06:22.792 --> 06:23.959
Over here!

06:29.458 --> 06:32.542
(creaking)

06:49.000 --> 06:51.000
(door opens, creaks)

07:05.500 --> 07:06.583
Hello?

07:08.125 --> 07:10.417
Fiona:
Oh, why don't you fuck off?

07:10.917 --> 07:12.917
You shouldn't break
into people's houses.

07:14.542 --> 07:16.959
-I fell over.
-Fiona, just give me my money.

07:17.041 --> 07:18.333
(Fiona yells)

07:19.041 --> 07:20.542
(knife scrapes)

07:22.041 --> 07:23.792
Jesus Christ.

07:23.875 --> 07:25.041
I've got this.

07:26.208 --> 07:27.792
Fiona.

07:27.875 --> 07:29.458
Did you call Laurence?

07:29.542 --> 07:31.667
When would I have the time
to call your husband?

07:32.208 --> 07:34.959
You know, I've barely had
the chance to send him this.

07:35.041 --> 07:36.792
(Billy and Ruby
moaning on phone)

07:36.875 --> 07:39.458
Oh, come on! Turn it off!

07:39.542 --> 07:40.959
What the fuck is that?!

07:41.750 --> 07:43.625
-You're so dead! Gimme that!
-Don't!

07:43.709 --> 07:44.834
Oh...

07:44.917 --> 07:46.458
Don't come
one step closer, okay?

07:46.542 --> 07:49.041
-Okay!
-Fucking traitor.
And you!

07:49.125 --> 07:51.166
-If you're gonna put
all your eggs in his--
-Billy: Look!

07:51.250 --> 07:53.834
I am sorry about
the meltdown with Jackie.

07:53.917 --> 07:55.917
And I'm sorry about
calling everybody cunts.

07:56.000 --> 07:58.333
And I know it's been sudden
and we've lost money,

07:58.417 --> 08:00.375
and that's all been hard
on you, but Jesus Christ,

08:00.458 --> 08:02.792
it's just money!
It isn't people!

08:02.875 --> 08:04.750
You can't really
care that much.

08:04.834 --> 08:06.000
(knife clinks)

08:06.083 --> 08:07.166
I mean,

08:07.250 --> 08:09.083
maybe you're just
in love with me, okay?

08:09.166 --> 08:10.375
-(laughs)
-If that's the case.

08:10.458 --> 08:11.875
then I know that
my being your boss

08:11.959 --> 08:13.083
would have been
hard on you, too.
And I get that.

08:13.166 --> 08:14.333
Okay, give it a rest,
Billy.

08:14.417 --> 08:15.834
-What? Don't you start!
-Just-- you know.

08:15.917 --> 08:17.458
I'm sure she's good without
the condescending speech,

08:17.542 --> 08:18.834
Ruby:
Jesus Christ. And also,

08:18.917 --> 08:20.750
money is important.
Maybe you don't know that

08:20.834 --> 08:22.750
'cause you've never
gone without it, you know?

08:22.834 --> 08:24.500
Fiona, did you call Laurence?

08:24.583 --> 08:26.208
-Just gimme the money!
-(Fiona grunts)

08:26.291 --> 08:27.959
(Ruby screams)

08:30.250 --> 08:31.625
Fiona:
I'm sorry...

08:32.542 --> 08:34.083
-Ow!
-She cut your finger!

08:35.417 --> 08:36.875
Hey! Hey!

08:37.375 --> 08:39.125
-(knife clatters)
-Ruby: I got it, I got it!

08:39.208 --> 08:41.000
♪ ♪

08:43.375 --> 08:45.959
-Did he tell you
about our plans?
-What plans?

08:46.041 --> 08:47.750
-Shut the fuck up.
-Fiona: Yeah.

08:47.834 --> 08:50.333
It's not the only secret
I've been keeping, now,
is it, Ruby?

08:50.417 --> 08:52.709
-What? What?
-Nothing. Just forget it.

08:52.792 --> 08:55.583
Yeah, just forget about
all those little people...

08:55.667 --> 08:57.834
-...wondering where you are.
-You know, I don't
know what she's--

08:57.917 --> 09:00.792
I know she's got
fucking kids, Fiona.

09:03.333 --> 09:05.333
You knew?

09:07.166 --> 09:09.500
I saw the picture on your phone.

09:11.875 --> 09:14.792
-Why didn't you say anything?
-Why didn't you say anything?

09:16.709 --> 09:19.375
That's why I couldn't sleep
with you on the train.

09:20.583 --> 09:21.667
Why?

09:24.542 --> 09:26.875
'Cause you thought that
I would have a flappy vagina?

09:27.834 --> 09:30.792
No! No, it was just--
it was just the thought

09:30.875 --> 09:32.625
of doing it with a mom,
you know?

09:32.709 --> 09:34.041
(Fiona scoffs)

09:34.125 --> 09:35.792
Of breaking up a family.
Of breaking up a family,
I meant.

09:35.875 --> 09:36.917
What the fuck!

09:37.000 --> 09:38.375
-No! Not like--
-Fiona: Billy. Billy!

09:38.458 --> 09:39.917
People come to you
for words,

09:40.000 --> 09:42.291
and yet all that
seems to flow out of
your mouth is shit!

09:44.000 --> 09:47.041
I... I've been spinning
your shit into gold

09:47.125 --> 09:49.458
for the past
seven years, and now...

09:49.542 --> 09:51.458
(tense music playing)

09:51.542 --> 09:52.875
you don't want it anymore.

09:54.166 --> 09:56.875
Well, you can take
my career away from me,

09:58.041 --> 09:59.500
but you can't take this.

09:59.583 --> 10:00.917
-No, what are you doing?
-No, no!

10:01.000 --> 10:02.208
Billy: Get the bag,
get the bag!

10:02.291 --> 10:03.709
-Fiona: Get off me!
-(cell phone ringing)

10:03.792 --> 10:06.291
-Billy: What are you doing?
-Fiona: Get off!

10:06.375 --> 10:09.625
(indistinct shouting continues)

10:09.709 --> 10:11.041
(phone clicks)

10:12.500 --> 10:15.208
-Hello?
-Laurence (on phone): Ruby.

10:15.291 --> 10:17.917
-(shouting continues)
-Uh, are you okay?

10:18.000 --> 10:20.291
-Laurence:
Where the fuck are you?
-I'm, uh...

10:20.375 --> 10:21.750
-Billy: No, shit! No!
-(Fiona shrieks)

10:21.834 --> 10:23.500
-(glass shatters)
-(arguing stops)

10:25.834 --> 10:27.333
Laurence:
Ruby! Are you listening?

10:27.417 --> 10:29.417
I need to talk to you now!

10:30.500 --> 10:32.500
Hey, Laurence,
I'm gonna have to call
you back in a few minutes.

10:32.583 --> 10:33.792
Laurence: No, no, no,
do not hang up on me!

10:33.875 --> 10:35.083
Don't hang up on me, Ruby!

10:35.166 --> 10:36.875
-I swear to God! You--
-(line disconnects)

10:45.917 --> 10:47.709
(stairs creaking)

11:00.417 --> 11:02.208
Where's Fiona?

11:04.083 --> 11:06.083
Don't look out
the window.

11:07.417 --> 11:08.583
Why?

11:19.458 --> 11:21.375
(birds chirping)

11:21.458 --> 11:22.875
Billy...

11:22.959 --> 11:24.625
I think she's dead.

11:26.375 --> 11:28.166
She won't be.

11:30.250 --> 11:32.458
-(footsteps)
-(insects chirping)

11:37.000 --> 11:38.417
-Oh...
-Oh.

11:39.458 --> 11:41.458
-(Billy retches)
-(gasps)

11:42.125 --> 11:43.750
(vomiting)

11:45.083 --> 11:46.291
(coughing)

11:50.792 --> 11:53.500
-(phone ringing)
-(breathing heavily)

11:57.625 --> 11:59.125
-(phone clicks)
-Laurence?

11:59.208 --> 12:02.458
-Ruby, what is happening?
-(Ruby crying)

12:02.875 --> 12:04.542
Laurence...

12:04.625 --> 12:05.667
(sighs)

12:05.750 --> 12:07.667
Baby, are you
having an affair?

12:08.542 --> 12:10.542
-What?
-Laurence: Just, are you--

12:10.625 --> 12:13.291
are you with him? Billy?

12:13.375 --> 12:15.000
Uh...

12:16.792 --> 12:18.333
Uh...

12:18.417 --> 12:20.458
Uh, wait, wait, what?

12:20.792 --> 12:22.583
If you tell me that you
are having an affair,

12:22.667 --> 12:24.834
our marriage is over. Are you?

12:26.667 --> 12:28.333
Our marriage will be over!

12:28.417 --> 12:31.083
♪ ♪

12:31.166 --> 12:32.375
Um... ye--

12:32.458 --> 12:34.709
(thunder rumbling)

12:38.083 --> 12:40.417
(heavy breathing)

12:45.125 --> 12:46.917
No.

12:47.291 --> 12:49.375
(sighing)

12:51.291 --> 12:53.375
You are at a yoga retreat

12:53.458 --> 12:55.583
in Malibu, right?

12:58.375 --> 13:00.542
Fuck, just say yes.

13:02.625 --> 13:04.208
Yes.

13:07.041 --> 13:09.208
Laurence:
Okay. Good.

13:10.166 --> 13:11.250
Um...

13:12.041 --> 13:13.625
I miss you,

13:13.709 --> 13:15.875
so I'm-- I'm gonna come
and get you. Just...

13:15.959 --> 13:18.125
text me the address
and I will see you there...

13:18.208 --> 13:20.041
-...5:00 on Friday. Okay?
-(sniffs) Oh, but, um--

13:20.125 --> 13:22.291
Five o'clock. I love you.

13:24.583 --> 13:26.583
♪ ♪

13:26.667 --> 13:28.417
Yeah, you, too.

13:31.333 --> 13:33.250
(phone clatters)

13:36.083 --> 13:38.250
(tense music playing)

13:46.458 --> 13:48.208
(sighs)

13:53.583 --> 13:54.709
(sniffs)

13:57.500 --> 13:58.959
-Hey.
-Hey.

13:59.041 --> 14:01.750
-We need to call an ambulance.
-No, no, no.

14:01.834 --> 14:04.375
Yeah, we-- or her Nan

14:04.458 --> 14:05.917
because her Nan
shouldn't see this.

14:06.000 --> 14:08.500
-Wait! No, no.
-I'm gonna get
her off the thing.

14:08.583 --> 14:11.458
Yeah. Or we get someone
out here, you know.

14:11.542 --> 14:14.083
-Where are we?
Where even are we?
-Wait. I-I don't know...

14:14.166 --> 14:17.709
-Do we have Wi-Fi here?
-No, no, wait!
Who would we call?

14:17.792 --> 14:20.917
-People.
People to get her off the...
-No.

14:21.000 --> 14:23.750
-...thing.
-Billy, Billy, um...

14:27.083 --> 14:28.959
I need you to leave with me.

14:29.041 --> 14:31.000
♪ ♪

14:31.583 --> 14:34.250
And we'll do
the right thing, okay?

14:34.333 --> 14:36.458
But I need you
to go with me now.

14:37.208 --> 14:38.542
Okay.

14:40.792 --> 14:43.000
-Billy: I got sick.
-Yeah.

14:44.125 --> 14:46.875
-You okay?
-Yeah. I'm sorry.

14:46.959 --> 14:49.000
♪ ♪

14:59.667 --> 15:01.875
Billy:
I got sick over there.

15:02.417 --> 15:04.500
Ruby:
Hang on, hang on, hang on.

15:04.583 --> 15:06.166
Wait!

15:09.000 --> 15:11.000
(drops bucket)

15:13.166 --> 15:14.375
(Billy sniffs)

15:17.458 --> 15:20.583
♪ ♪

15:23.041 --> 15:24.667
Wait...

15:26.333 --> 15:27.458
(exhales)

15:27.542 --> 15:29.208
The money.

15:31.125 --> 15:32.917
-I'll get it.
-(quietly): Okay.

15:33.000 --> 15:36.083
♪ ♪

16:02.250 --> 16:05.750
(tense music playing)

16:30.959 --> 16:32.125
Billy: Which way?

16:32.208 --> 16:33.667
Ruby:
Do you see that?

16:33.750 --> 16:35.500
-Is that a person?
-Billy: Who's that?

16:35.583 --> 16:39.792
Ruby:
Okay. Um, just let me
do the talking.

16:40.875 --> 16:43.417
♪ ♪

16:44.291 --> 16:45.542
-Ruby: Hello.
-(woman gasps)

16:45.625 --> 16:46.667
Ruby: Hi.

16:46.750 --> 16:49.166
-Sorry, ma'am.
-Hello.

16:49.250 --> 16:50.834
Hello. Um...

16:52.000 --> 16:53.542
Oh.

16:53.625 --> 16:54.875
Are you busy?

16:54.959 --> 16:57.041
No, I was just checking
on this badger here.

16:57.125 --> 16:59.542
-Do you think--
-Is the badger okay?

16:59.959 --> 17:01.959
Well, no, I'd say
she's completely dead.

17:05.041 --> 17:08.375
Um, we-we need to get
to a train station.

17:08.458 --> 17:10.041
-How'd you get out here?
-Ruby: We hiked.

17:10.125 --> 17:11.875
-Woman: You hiked? Oh.
-Yeah.

17:11.959 --> 17:14.250
And we got lost.
(laughs)

17:14.333 --> 17:15.417
Um...

17:15.500 --> 17:17.417
could you take us
to the nearest station?

17:17.500 --> 17:19.834
Oh, well, that'd be
Trinidad Central.

17:20.291 --> 17:22.583
Ruby:
Could you take us there?

17:22.667 --> 17:24.166
The station's that way...

17:25.291 --> 17:27.083
and I was heading...

17:27.166 --> 17:29.166
that way. Are you okay?

17:32.000 --> 17:34.166
I left my coat
on the train.

17:35.667 --> 17:37.834
It was a really
great coat.

17:39.125 --> 17:41.709
Ruby:
Yeah, we need to get
to LA really soon

17:41.792 --> 17:44.041
because his mother...

17:44.125 --> 17:45.500
has cancer.

17:45.583 --> 17:48.917
-Why my mother?
-Yeah, I know, exactly.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.250
Oh, I'm sorry to hear that.

17:51.333 --> 17:53.458
My mom had cancer, too.

17:56.750 --> 17:58.125
-(Billy crying)
-Oh no. I...

17:58.208 --> 18:00.583
How long does she...?
Is it-- I--

18:00.667 --> 18:03.291
Tell me something nice
about her!

18:05.542 --> 18:06.709
(gasps)

18:08.500 --> 18:10.834
She used to put my
toothbrush in the toilet

18:10.917 --> 18:13.166
when I forgot
to brush my teeth.

18:14.667 --> 18:16.083
Woman: Uh...

18:22.417 --> 18:23.458
(car door opens)

18:23.542 --> 18:25.542
-Is that nice?
-(shushes)

18:25.625 --> 18:27.208
(car door closes)

18:31.375 --> 18:33.667
-You put this on.
-Thanks.

18:33.750 --> 18:35.875
You help me get this
badger in the van,

18:35.959 --> 18:38.125
I'll give you
guys a ride.

