for the animals.

18:52.625 --> 18:54.166
Which animals?

18:54.250 --> 18:55.917
-Oh, just the dead ones.
-Billy: Dead ones?

18:56.000 --> 18:59.250
Beavers, yeah, dead beavers,
dead prairie dogs.

18:59.834 --> 19:01.500
Just anything dead, really.

19:01.583 --> 19:03.583
There's a lot of
roadkill around here.

19:03.667 --> 19:05.834
No one touches it.
It's such a waste.

19:06.709 --> 19:09.583
People don't really
know what to do when
they see a dead thing.

19:10.625 --> 19:13.291
I've just always felt
very comfortable with them.

19:14.083 --> 19:17.125
Once they're stuffed,
they all but come back to life.

19:17.750 --> 19:20.250
-Are you a taxidermist?
-Yeah, that's me.

19:20.333 --> 19:22.458
Oh... Oh, thank God.

19:25.250 --> 19:29.917
♪ You go back,
Jack, do it again ♪

19:30.000 --> 19:31.625
♪ Wheels turnin' 'round... ♪

19:31.709 --> 19:33.458
(lightning, thunder)

19:33.542 --> 19:35.709
-Ruby: Thank you so much.
-Woman: Of course.

19:35.792 --> 19:38.000
-He can keep the coat.
-(wind blowing)

19:38.792 --> 19:41.041
-Oh.
-Ruby: Oh God, I'm so sorry.

19:41.125 --> 19:44.166
-Oh, no!
-Billy. Billy!

19:44.250 --> 19:45.834
Billy!

19:53.333 --> 19:54.792
-Thank you.
-Sorry.

19:56.083 --> 19:57.709
